<subSubSection id="798213AC5C6DFFDAFF36FD47DB4CA7A7" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" type="description">
<paragraph id="312740275C6DFFDAFF36FD47D8A4A0A3" blockId="4.[178,1085,643,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
D e s c r i p t i o n: 
<quantity id="F660EDC25C6DFFDAFE13FD40D88EA0CB" box="[407,489,643,665]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFD01FD40DBB5A0CB" box="[645,722,643,665]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
. Coloration: head dark brown with anterior part paler; pronotum dark brown with paler margins; elytra reddish brown; abdomen dark brown, with posterior margins of segments somewhat paler; legs and antennae yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="312740275C6DFFDAFF36FCC2D85EA194" blockId="4.[178,1086,769,966]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
Head approximately as wide as long; puncturation dense and shallow, interstices distinctly narrower than diameter of punctures and with distinct microsculpture. Eyes approximately as long as postocular region in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFC95FCF8DA06A103" box="[785,865,827,849]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
). Antennae (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFC6DFCF8DD51A103" box="[1001,1078,827,849]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
) distinctly incrassate apically; antennomere IV approximately as long as wide; V-X of increasing width and increasingly transverse; X strongly transverse, approximately twice as wide as long. Maxillary palpi with preapical palpomeres approximately 2.5 times as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="312740275C6DFFDAFF36FC15DD5AA674" blockId="4.[178,1086,982,1062]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
Pronotum 1.21 times as wide as long and 1.25 times as wide as head; maximal width in anterior half; posterior angles marked; lateral margins in posterior half weakly concave in dorsal view; puncturation very dense and ill-defined; microsculpture shallow (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFC61FBD3DD56A674" box="[997,1073,1040,1062]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="312740275C6DFFDAFF36FBF6DB33A692" blockId="4.[178,1086,1077,1216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
Elytra approximately as long as pronotum; humeral angles pronounced; posterior margins strongly sinuate near posterior angles; puncturation coarse (much more so than that of pronotum), dense, and somewhat granulose (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFD57FBB3DA44A6D4" box="[723,803,1136,1158]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
); microsculpture indistinct. Hind wings apparently fully developed. Legs slender; metatarsomere I approximately as long as the combined length of II and III.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="312740275C6DFFDAFF36FB13DAA7A72A" blockId="4.[178,1086,1232,1400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
Abdomen with segments III-VI subparallel; segments III-V with pronounced anterior impressions, segment VI with shallow impression; anterior impressions of segments III- VI with conspicuously coarse and dense puncturation; remainder of tergal surfaces of segments III-VI with rather fine and moderately sparse puncturation; puncturation of tergite VII slightly granulose; tergites III-V without, tergites VI-VII with very shallow microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFCECFAA1DAD2A72A" box="[872,949,1378,1400]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="312740275C6DFFDAFF36FA4BDB4CA7A7" blockId="4.[178,1085,1415,1525]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
6: tergites VII and VIII with pronounced median keel (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFD69FA44DA03A7CF" box="[749,868,1415,1437]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Figs 65, 67</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly concave in the middle (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFD07FA66DBB4A7E9" box="[643,723,1445,1467]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
); sternite VII unmodified; sternite VIII broadly convex posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFD81FA01DB36A78A" box="[517,593,1474,1496]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus slender (
<figureCitation id="A9A35CA25C6DFFDAFC3BFA01DD56A78A" box="[959,1073,1474,1496]" captionStart="Figs 63-71" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1340,1360]" captionTargetBox="[183,1080,212,1313]" captionTargetId="figure-4@19.[178,1091,370,849]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 63-71: Leptusa puetzi nov.sp.: (63) habitus; (64) forebody; (65) abdominal segments III-VII; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical part of median lobe in ventral view; (71) apical lobe of paramere. Scale bars: 63:L 1.0 mm; 64-65: 0.5 mm; 66-68: 0.2 mm; 69-71: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4523646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4523646/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Figs 69-70</figureCitation>
); apical lobe of paramere as in 
