<subSubSection id="798213AC5C6CFFDBFF36FEDEDBE5A069" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="312740275C6CFFDBFF36FEDEDBE5A069" blockId="5.[178,1086,285,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: 
<taxonomicName id="F6983BA45C6CFFDBFD8EFEDDDBC7A361" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2008" box="[522,672,286,307]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puetzi">
<emphasis id="03EC9C355C6CFFDBFD8EFEDDDBC7A361" box="[522,672,286,307]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Leptusa puetzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all its congeners especially by the distinctive morphology of the median lobe of the aedeagus. The species is attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="F6983BA45C6CFFDBFED4FE9BDB48A33E" authority="PACE" authorityName="PACE" box="[336,559,344,366]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Drepanoleptusa">
<emphasis id="03EC9C355C6CFFDBFED4FE9BD894A33C" box="[336,499,344,366]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Drepanoleptusa</emphasis>
PACE
</taxonomicName>
especially based on the morphology of the median lobe of the aedeagus, which is rather similar to that of 
<emphasis id="03EC9C355C6CFFDBFD6EFEB5DAE0A3D9" box="[746,903,373,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">L. sichuanensis</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F6983BA45C6CFFDBFC3FFEB5DD51A3D9" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2008" box="[955,1078,373,395]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stimulans">
<emphasis id="03EC9C355C6CFFDBFC3FFEB5DD51A3D9" box="[955,1078,373,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">L. stimulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From the latter, which was collected in the same locality, the species is additionally distinguished by smaller size, paler coloration, different morphology of the antennae, completely different puncturation of the whole body, the completely different shape and chaetotaxy of the apical lobe of the paramere, and the different male secondary sexual characters. For illustrations of other 
<taxonomicName id="F6983BA45C6CFFDBFDA7FDC4DBA1A04F" box="[547,710,519,541]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Drepanoleptusa">
<emphasis id="03EC9C355C6CFFDBFDA7FDC4DBA1A04F" box="[547,710,519,541]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Drepanoleptusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known from 
<collectingCountry id="498F00B75C6CFFDBFC1AFDC4DABDA04F" box="[926,986,519,541]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">China</collectingCountry>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="55093DD65C6CFFDBFB83FDCBD988A069" author="PACE R" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="751 - 760" refId="ref9671" refString="PACE R. (1997): Specie del genere Leptusa in Cina. Monografia del genere Leptusa KRAATZ: Supplemento VII (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue suisse de Zoologie 104: 751 - 760." type="journal article" year="1997">PACE (1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="55093DD65C6CFFDBFF7EFDE6D848A069" author="PACE R" box="[250,303,549,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="369 - 376" refId="ref9710" refString="PACE R. (1999): Nuove Leptusa della Cina. Monografia del genere Leptusa KRAATZ: Supplemento X (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Berlin 49: 369 - 376." type="journal article" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="55093DD65C6CFFDBFEBDFDE6D80AA069" author="PACE R" box="[313,365,549,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="151 - 160" refId="ref9748" refString="PACE R. (2001): Nuove specie cinesi del genere Leptusa. Monografia del genere Leptusa KRAATZ: Supplemento XII (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino 18: 151 - 160." type="journal article" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="55093DD65C6CFFDBFE22FDE6DB52A069" author="ASSING V" box="[422,565,549,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="971 - 1019" refId="ref9459" refString="ASSING V. (2002): New species and records of Leptusa KRAATZ from the Palaearctic region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 34 (2): 971 - 1019." type="journal article" year="2002">ASSING (2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="55093DD65C6CFFDBFDC4FDE6DB10A069" author="ASSING V" box="[576,631,549,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="1157 - 1174" refId="ref9582" refString="ASSING V. (2006): Six new species and additional records of Leptusa from northern Yunnan, China (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 38 (2): 1157 - 1174." type="journal article" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="798213AC5C6CFFDBFF36FD88DB42A0C8" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="312740275C6CFFDBFF36FD88DB42A0C8" blockId="5.[178,1086,586,666]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
